						               													<description>In this travel version of a Pachisi descendant, up to four players attempt to move their four pawns one lap around the board, and into their home.  Landing a pawn exactly on one of four points on the track allows the player to hop that pawn along those four points, for a large shortcut.  Also, should the player roll a one, the pawn can move into the center for an even greater shortcut, since that pawn may exit to the final shortcut point before its home.  A pawn occupying a space to which an opponent's pawn is moving becomes &amp;quot;aggravated&amp;quot; and sent back to base.  Unlike Pachisi, there is no opportunity to form blockades for safety of the pawns and obstruction of the path.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
